q: In a college, there are 1500 students who go to any one of the classes, out of the four different classes viz. dance, music, painting & cooking. The ratio of the number of boys and girls among them is 7:8. 40% of the total girls go to the dance class and 55% of the total girls go to painting class. The total number of students going to music class is 240. 230 students go to cooking class. The ratio of the number of girls and the number of boys who go to paint class is 2:1. 30% of the total number of boys go to music class. 370 students go to dancing class. What effect would it make on the number of girls going to music class if the percentage of boys going to music class is changed from 30% to 35%?
